    "Based on this analysis, ref.",
    "150 finds that the average basicity of the CDR3 (on the β chain), as well as basicity and hydrophobicity of the amino acids in the CDR3β center, play an important role at discriminating epitope-specific from unspecific sequences.",
    "Explainable predictions can be obtained in a model-agnostic fashion by applying interpretability pipelines, for example the one estimating 'anchors' 158.",
    "An anchor is an explanation that 'anchors' the model's prediction locally to specific data attributes and formulated as an if-then rule.",
    "Once applied to models for classification of TCRs by epitope specificity 159, anchors recapitulate the presence of specific amino acids in certain positions of epitope-specific TCR sequences (Fig. 4b), for example polar amino acids like serine (S) in the CDR3β binding to the peptide KLGGALQAK 159."
